Reasoning: The paper presents a novel algorithm for synthesizing motion policies based on Riemannian Motion Policies (RMPs), which are commonly used in robotics and control systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of computational graphs and sparse structure for computational efficiency, which suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The stability analysis and experimental results on high-DOF manipulation systems may also relate to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
